    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thank you. At a minimum, this represents a consensus change and each version should be a major version.\r\n\r\nSo London would be 7.0.0 or something.\r\n\r\nIf there is a change that is not breaking, possibly a a new optional way to compress data between peers, that would be a 7.1.0 release on top of that.\r\n\r\nI'm not exactly sure how the decisions are made for choosing the next hardfork. But if EIPs are added one at a time and the trigger can be pulled any time, then yes I agree a new 7.0.0rc1 is appropriate each time.\r\n\r\nBut if inclusions EIPs are just discussions and there is actually only one decision to launch to testnet, then maybe only need to release an RC every time there is a deployment on testnet.",
